    "description": "SPK Corporation, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the trading of automotive spare parts and accessories, and industrial vehicle parts in Japan, Asia, Oceania, Central America, and South America. The company offers engines, drivetrain, brakes, suspension, electrical, and air conditioning parts; and oil chemical products. It also supplies automotive aftermarket parts and accessories; and machinery parts and components, including multifunction displays, integrated switches, dials, telematics equipment, and electrical components, such as lamps, resin parts, and functional parts to the manufacturers of construction vehicles, forklifts, and tractors. The company was formerly known as Daido Automobile Enterprising Co., Ltd. and changed its name to SPK Corporation in 1992. SPK Corporation was incorporated in 1917 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan."
